A **genesis block** is the first block of a [[block_chain]]. Modern versions of Bitcoin assign it block number 0, though older versions gave it number 1.

## Main network genesis block
[The block on Bitcoin Block Explorer](http://blockexplorer.com/block/000000000019d6689c085ae165831e934ff763ae46a2a6c172b3f1b60a8ce26f)

Here is a representation of the genesis block as it appeared in a comment in an old version of Bitcoin ([line 1613](http://bitcoin.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/bitcoin/trunk/main.cpp?revision=133&view=markup&pathrev=170)). The first section defines exactly all of the variables necessary to recreate the block. The second section is the block in standard printblock format, which contains shortened versions of the data in the first section.

